msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:399
msgid ""
"A `ProgrammingError` is raised if this method is used outside of a TPC "
"transaction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:402
msgid ""
"After calling `!tpc_prepare()`, no statements can be executed until "
"`tpc_commit()` or `tpc_rollback()` will be called."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:406
msgid "The |PREPARE TRANSACTION|_ PostgreSQL command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/connection.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.connection.Connection.tpc_commit:1
#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/connection_async.py:docstring
#: psycopg.connection_async.AsyncConnection.tpc_commit:1
msgid "Commit a prepared two-phase transaction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:417
msgid ""
"When called with no arguments, `!tpc_commit()` commits a TPC transaction "
"previously prepared with `tpc_prepare()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:420
msgid ""
"If `!tpc_commit()` is called prior to `!tpc_prepare()`, a single phase "
"commit is performed.  A transaction manager may choose to do this if only a "
"single resource is participating in the global transaction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:424
msgid ""
"When called with a transaction ID `!xid`, the database commits the given "
"transaction.  If an invalid transaction ID is provided, a `ProgrammingError` "
"will be raised.  This form should be called outside of a transaction, and is "
"intended for use in recovery."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:429 ../../../api/connections.rst:450
msgid "On return, the TPC transaction is ended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:431
msgid "The |COMMIT PREPARED|_ PostgreSQL command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/connection.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.connection.Connection.tpc_rollback:1
#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/connection_async.py:docstring
#: psycopg.connection_async.AsyncConnection.tpc_rollback:1
msgid "Roll back a prepared two-phase transaction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:442
msgid ""
"When called with no arguments, `!tpc_rollback()` rolls back a TPC "
"transaction.  It may be called before or after `tpc_prepare()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:445
msgid ""
"When called with a transaction ID `!xid`, it rolls back the given "
"transaction.  If an invalid transaction ID is provided, a `ProgrammingError` "
"is raised.  This form should be called outside of a transaction, and is "
"intended for use in recovery."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:452
msgid "The |ROLLBACK PREPARED|_ PostgreSQL command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:460
msgid ""
"Returns a list of `Xid` representing pending transactions, suitable for use "
"with `tpc_commit()` or `tpc_rollback()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:463
msgid ""
"If a transaction was not initiated by Psycopg, the returned Xids will have "
"attributes `~Xid.format_id` and `~Xid.bqual` set to `!None` and the `~Xid."
"gtrid` set to the PostgreSQL transaction ID: such Xids are still usable for "
"recovery.  Psycopg uses the same algorithm of the `PostgreSQL JDBC driver`__ "
"to encode a XA triple in a string, so transactions initiated by a program "
"using such driver should be unpacked correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/connections.rst:473
msgid ""
"Xids returned by `!tpc_recover()` also have extra attributes `~Xid."
"prepared`, `~Xid.owner`, `~Xid.database` populated with the values read from "
"the server."
msgstr ""

